{
  "texts": [
    "These neural patterns are critical for distinguishing between similar smells and contribute to robust odor perception.",
    "AI methods can model this process by learning how sensory inputs correspond to structured activation maps.",
    "By analyzing these spatiotemporal patterns, AI supports the interpretation of neural coding in the olfactory bulb.",
    "This approach enhances our understanding of how the brain represents odors and informs the design of artificial systems for odor classification and detection.",
    "Recent studies employing advanced imaging techniques, such as functional magnetic resonance imaging (fMRI) and calcium imaging, have provided new insights into how the brain encodes and interprets odors (Boot et al. 2024)."
  ]
}